{"article_id":"9ypq4CGQjFhLUBmV","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"Cybersecurity expert :","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"North Korea `` may have disconnected themselves ''","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"Research company says","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"North Korea 's Internet goes back down ,","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"only to return","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"Monday 's Web blackout lasted more than nine hours ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"according to Dyn Research","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"Web disruption came amid escalating war of words between the U.S. , North Korea","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"North Koreans ' ability","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"to surf the Internet","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"-- for the few in the isolated nation","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"who could ever really go online anyway --","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"is rockier than ever .","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"Dyn Research reported on Monday","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"that the country 's Internet was down , after 24 hours of `` increasing instability . ''","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"It stayed dead for more than nine hours ,","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"then came back to life","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"-- but not for long .","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"Half a day later","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"Dyn said","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"it was down again .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"Then it was back up , at about 1 a.m. Wednesday Pyongyang time","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"( 11 a.m. Tuesday ET ) ,","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"the company said .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"But the assessment of Dyn , a company","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"that monitors Internet performance worldwide ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"made earlier Tuesday ,","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"did not change :","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"`` North Korea continues its struggles","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"to stay online . ''","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"How to hack Sony","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"How to hack Sony","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"02:21","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"Making fun of Kim is 'path to death '","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"Making fun of Kim is 'path to death '","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"02:04","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"The timing of North Korea 's latest Internet issues makes them significant .","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"They come","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"days after the U.S. government blamed Pyongyang for being behind the hacking of Sony Pictures over that company 's production of `` The Interview ''","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"-- a comedy","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"depicting the assassination of North Korean leader Kim Jong Un --","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"as well as threats against anyone","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"who dared watch the movie .","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"North Korea denied any responsibility ,","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"even as it blamed the U.S. government for being behind the making of the Seth Rogen-James Franco film .","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"Its totalitarian government went on to officially make its own threat ,","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"warning the United States","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"that its `` citadels '' will be attacked ,","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"dwarfing the hacking attack on Sony .","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"Pyongyang has n't leveled any blame or threats about its latest Internet outage .","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"But experts are skeptical","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"that the American government had any involvement .","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"That 's almost irrelevant ,","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"said Mike Chinoy , a frequent traveler to North Korea and former CNN correspondent .","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"`` The issue ... is not whether it was","depth":14},{"id":62,"text":"or it was n't ( the United States","depth":14},{"id":63,"text":"that knocked out North Korea 's Internet ) .","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"The issue is what","depth":14},{"id":65,"text":"the North Koreans think","depth":15},{"id":66,"text":"it was , ''","depth":15},{"id":67,"text":"said Chinoy , a U.S.-China Institute senior fellow .","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"`` And I think","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"it 's safe to assume","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"-- unless they themselves took their system offline for their own security ,","depth":15},{"id":71,"text":"which is not impossible --","depth":15},{"id":72,"text":"they 'll be looking to respond . ''","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"Expert :","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"Could be ' a 15-year-old in a Guy Fawkes mask '","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"Unlike the Sony cyberattack and threats ,","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"which were linked to a group","depth":14},{"id":77,"text":"called `` Guardians of Peace , ''","depth":14},{"id":78,"text":"the latest issues have n't been tied to any group or government .","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"It 's possible they have nothing to do with the Sony dust-up","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"and are simply an internal matter .","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"Another possibility :","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"North Korea 's Internet traffic is routed through China ,","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"so issues or officials there may be to blame .","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"Another option :","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"it could be a deliberate move by the country 's own government .","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"`` North Korea may have disconnected themselves ,","depth":14},{"id":87,"text":"either preemptively","depth":16},{"id":88,"text":"to prevent that movie from being distributed ,","depth":16},{"id":89,"text":"but also , probably more likely , in a defensive posture , ''","depth":15},{"id":90,"text":"said Shawn Henry , a cybersecurity expert and former executive assistant director of the FBI .","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"Talking","depth":14},{"id":92,"text":"when North Korea 's Internet was totally down ,","depth":14},{"id":93,"text":"Dyn Research 's Doug Madory said","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"`` usually there are isolated blips '' anyway in the country 's service .","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"But he thinks","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"what happened here was different .","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"`` I would n't be surprised","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"if they are absorbing some sort of attack , ''","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"Madory said .","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"U.S. State Department spokeswoman Marie Harf deflected a question about the disruption .","depth":6},{"id":101,"text":"`` We are n't going to discuss","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"-- you know --","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"publicly , operational details about the possible response options or comment on those kind of reports in any way ,","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"except to say","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"as we implement our responses ,","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"some will be seen ,","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"some may not be seen , ''","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"she said .","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"What are military options for N. Korea ?","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"What are military options for N. Korea ?","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"01:48","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":6},{"id":117,"text":"New North Korea threats to attack U.S.","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"New North Korea threats to attack U.S.","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"02:12","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"No one is saying","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"the U.S. government could n't have carried out such an attack .","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"But tech experts say","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"it might not have needed to ,","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"given the ability of anyone , anywhere","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"to do something like this .","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"What happened with Sony , especially the studio 's decision","depth":6},{"id":129,"text":"to shelve","depth":6},{"id":130,"text":"-- at least temporarily --","depth":6},{"id":131,"text":"the release of `` The Interview , ''","depth":6},{"id":132,"text":"got a lot of people upset .","depth":5},{"id":133,"text":"Matthew Prince , president of the performance and security company CloudFlare , told CNN","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"he could n't say definitively","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"that there was an attack at all .","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"if there was ,","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"he said","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"it 's possible a lone individual , not an entire government , was behind it .","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"`` If it is an attack ,","depth":8},{"id":141,"text":"it 's highly unlikely","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"it 's the United States .","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"More likely it 's a 15-year-old in a Guy Fawkes mask , ''","depth":7},{"id":144,"text":"said Prince ,","depth":7},{"id":145,"text":"tying the prospective attackers to those","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"connected to or inspired by the hacktivist movement Anonymous .","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"Do these outages equal outrage ,","depth":6},{"id":148,"text":"leaving North Koreans unable to view `` Gangnam Style '' for the 2-billionth-plus time ?","depth":6},{"id":149,"text":"Have they been frustrated","depth":7},{"id":150,"text":"when they tried to check on the latest NBA results for their fantasy teams","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"or engage in heated debates about local , national and international politics ?","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"No .","depth":6},{"id":153,"text":"There 's a reason","depth":7},{"id":154,"text":"the Committee","depth":8},{"id":155,"text":"to Protect Journalists ranks North Korea second on its list of `` Most Censored Countries .","depth":8},{"id":156,"text":"'' Only a smattering of `` ruling elites '' can go online freely ,","depth":8},{"id":157,"text":"leaving the public limited to a `` heavily monitored and censored","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"( intranet )","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"network with no connections to the outside world , ''","depth":9},{"id":160,"text":"according to the advocacy group .","depth":7},{"id":161,"text":"Widespread computer technology overall is n't a reality in one of the world 's poorest and ,","depth":7},{"id":162,"text":"according to many outsiders ,","depth":8},{"id":163,"text":"most antiquated countries .","depth":8},{"id":164,"text":"2012 report from KISA , South Korea 's Internet development agency , noted","depth":9},{"id":165,"text":"North Korea then had only 1,024 IP addresses","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"-- unique numbers","depth":12},{"id":167,"text":"assigned to every device","depth":13},{"id":168,"text":"that logs on to the Internet --","depth":13},{"id":169,"text":"in a country of about 25 million people .","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"That figure may not exactly reflect the current usage","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"since , for example , people can use one IP address for several items ,","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"but it 's still paltry by any modern measure .","depth":9},{"id":173,"text":"The United States has more than 1.5 billion IP addresses .","depth":7},{"id":174,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":175,"text":"Defector :","depth":9},{"id":176,"text":"N. Korea running hacker network","depth":9},{"id":177,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":7},{"id":178,"text":"MUST WATCH Defector :","depth":7},{"id":179,"text":"N. Korea running hacker network","depth":7},{"id":180,"text":"01:44","depth":7},{"id":181,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":10},{"id":182,"text":"North Korea slams U.S. government","depth":10},{"id":183,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":9},{"id":184,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":10},{"id":185,"text":"North Korea slams U.S. government","depth":10},{"id":186,"text":"01:54","depth":9},{"id":187,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":9},{"id":188,"text":"Hacking :","depth":10},{"id":189,"text":"Did we underestimate N. Korea ?","depth":10},{"id":190,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":191,"text":"MUST WATCH Hacking :","depth":9},{"id":192,"text":"Did we underestimate N. Korea ?","depth":9},{"id":193,"text":"05:19","depth":8},{"id":194,"text":"Still ,","depth":6},{"id":195,"text":"even if most North Koreans are n't Web-savvy by design ,","depth":7},{"id":196,"text":"a dangerous handful of them may be .","depth":7},{"id":197,"text":"Jang Se-yul ,","depth":10},{"id":198,"text":"who claims","depth":11},{"id":199,"text":"he worked as a computer expert for North Korea 's government","depth":12},{"id":200,"text":"before defecting seven years ago ,","depth":12},{"id":201,"text":"told CNN","depth":9},{"id":202,"text":"he thinks","depth":9},{"id":203,"text":"that Pyongyang has 1,800 cyberwarriors","depth":10},{"id":204,"text":"stationed around the world .","depth":10},{"id":205,"text":"He says","depth":8},{"id":206,"text":"even the agents themselves do n't know","depth":9},{"id":207,"text":"how many others work for the secretive group","depth":11},{"id":208,"text":"-- called Bureau 121 --","depth":11},{"id":209,"text":"whose mission is to `` conduct cyberattacks against overseas and enemy states . ''","depth":10},{"id":210,"text":"An FBI investigation linked the malware , infrastructure and techniques","depth":9},{"id":211,"text":"used by the Guardians of Peace in the Sony attack","depth":9},{"id":212,"text":"to previous North Korean cyberattacks .","depth":8},{"id":213,"text":"After that , U.S. President Barack Obama called the hack `` an act of cybervandalism","depth":9},{"id":214,"text":"that was very costly , very expensive , ''","depth":9},{"id":215,"text":"though he stopped sort of calling it an act of war .","depth":8},{"id":216,"text":"The next question is :","depth":4},{"id":217,"text":"Will Kim , in Pyongyang , say the same about his country 's Internet issues ?","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":435,"left":347,"right":434,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":347,"left":248,"right":346,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":248,"left":0,"right":247,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":247,"left":225,"right":246,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":225,"left":219,"right":224,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":219,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":224,"left":223,"right":8,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":223,"left":221,"right":222,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":221,"left":3,"right":220,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":220,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":222,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":246,"left":229,"right":245,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":229,"left":228,"right":13,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":228,"left":226,"right":227,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":226,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":227,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":245,"left":239,"right":244,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":239,"left":230,"right":238,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":230,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":238,"left":232,"right":237,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":2